title: Cause and Effect Check
subtitle: Addressing Root Causes
new-page: true

Facilyn: The first context check asks a crucial question: "Does this action address the root cause of the problem?" This helps you avoid treating symptoms while ignoring underlying causes.

Facilyn: Think about your example decision. What problem or need is driving this choice?

How would you evaluate your decision against this check?

